enum BtResultCode
 

Result codes for Bluetooth stack operations.

When the Bluetooth C-API receives a operation for execution, it returns a value that describes state of the submitted operation. BtResult is an enumeration type that describes this state.
This state is found in two places. On the one side it is the return code of member functions, on the ohter hand it is found in the additional data that is embedded in the various result messages sent back from the Bluetooth stack to APOXI. The possible return values of the various member functions also depend on the kind of execution: Synchronous or asynchonous.

Enumerator:
BtRcAccepted 
BtRcPending 
BtRcOk 
BtRcRejected 
BtRcIgnored 
BtRcError 
BtRcUnknown

BOOLEAN ConvertUtf8ToWString (  const CHAR *  utf_char_pointer,
WString &  w_string
) 
 

Convert UTF-8 character array to WString object.

The character coding for Bluetooth is UTF-8. This means that all strings are transmitted in the UTF-8 character set. To enable APOXI, which works with unicode strings, a normal string treatment this functions performs a conversion from an UTF-8 character array to an Unicode WString.

Parameters:
utf_char_pointer Pointer to a CHAR containing the UTF-8 coded character array that should be converted.
w_string A reference to a WString, where to store the converted character array.
Returns:
TRUE: The conversion worked and w_string can be used.
FALSE: The conversion failed, do not use the w_string returned.

BtProfile ToProfile (  btapi_profile_t  profile  ) 
 

Convert stack profile type to APOXI profile type.

Some parameters to stack functions also as paramters to stack callback functions contain the type of profile. To and From the stack there is the C-API related type btapi_profile_t required. In APOXI the type BtProfile is used. The function ToProfile performs the task of converting the stack type to the APOXI type.

Parameters:
profile 

BtResultCode ToResultCode (  btapi_result_t  result  ) 
 

Convert stack result code to APOXI result code.

The result parameter of the stack callback functions is the stack defined C-API type btapi_result_t. To enable further processing this result code must be converted to the APOXI defined type BtResultCode. This task is performed by ToResultCode. result A btapi_result_t containing the C-API result code, that should be converted to the APOXI result code.

Returns:
A BtResultCode containing the APOXI representation of the passed in C-API result code.
